window.bookSummaryJSON = "<b>Fierce, monstrous dark dragons. Powerful, ancient magic. True, genuine friendship. </b><br><br><b><i>He doesnâ€™t remember he is supposed to save the world. </i></b><br><br>In the war-torn realm of the Worforgon, King Arken Shadowborn leads a relentless army of dragon-riding warriors, spreading chaos and fear. Amidst the devastation, a man named Stone emerges, reborn from a forgotten grave, his past a blank canvas.<br><br>Stone grapples not only with the external chaos but also the tumult within himself. His journey is not merely a physical one; it is a soul-searching odyssey into the heart of his own identity. Forgotten memories claw at the edges of his consciousness, a constant reminder of the mystery that shrouds his purpose. The burden of being the prophesized savior weighs heavily on Stone's shoulders, a mantle he never sought.<br><br>In the company of his loyal friends, Ceres and Adler, Stone embarks on a quest that transcends the physical realm. The Mountain of the Mystics beckons, and the Majestic Wilds hold the key to unlocking the prophecy. Each step forward is a struggle against the unknown, a journey into the depths of self-discovery.<br><br>As Stone faces the formidable Arken Shadowborn and his draconic army, the emotional turmoil within him mirrors the raging battles on the war-torn landscape. The Dark King's malevolence casts a long shadow over Stone's resolve, testing the very core of his being. Doubt, fear, and the weight of an entire world's hope converge in a tempest within his soul.<br><br><i>Riders of Dark Dragons is now Complete! This 5-book series begins here with Mystics on the Mountain and concludes with War of the Mystics.</i>"; 
